(by Deniz Esen, Econ Dimension GmbH, www.econdimension.com)\n\nConvert multiple codefiles or Visual Studio projects between VB.NET and C#.\n\nUsage:\nnetvertcmd LANGUAGE FOLDER [OUTPUT_FOLDER] [/F=Wildcard] [/R] [/W]\n LANGUAGE       = Use VBTOCS to convert codefiles from Visual Basic to C#\n                  or CSTOVB to convert codefiles from C# to Visual Basic\n                  or VBTOCSPROJ to convert projects from Visual Basic to C#\n                  or CSTOVBPROJ to convert projects from C# to Visual Basic\n FOLDER         = Source Folder\n OUTPUT_FOLDER  = (Optional) Target Folder\n                  Default is same as Source Folder\n /F=Wildcard    = (Optional) Filename or Wildcard\n                  Default is *.vb for VBTOCS or *.cs for CSTOVB\n                  or *.vbproj for VBTOCSPROJ or *.csproj for CSTOVBPROJ\n /R             = Recurse subdirectories\n /W             = Overwrite existing files\n\nExamples:\nnetvertcmd VBTOCS "C:\VBFiles" "C:\ConvertedCSFiles" /F=*.vb /R\nnetvertcmd VBTOCSPROJ "C:\VBProjects" /F=MyVBProject1.vbproj /W
